TITLE: Utah avalanche sparks shelter-in-place order at ski resort
SUMMARY: Snowbird, a mountain resort in Little Cottonwood Canyon southeast of Salt Lake City, said that after an hourslong search, "no guests or employees were caught in the debris caused by an avalanche" on Thursday

TITLE: Can you use Ozempic and Wegovy to shed a few pounds quickly?
SUMMARY: For short-term weight loss, drugs like semaglutide aren't the answer

TITLE: Man pleads guilty to manslaughter in robbery killing of rapper Pop Smoke
SUMMARY: Pop Smoke, the 20-year-old New York rapper whose legal name was Bashar Barakah Jackson, was killed on Feb. 19, 2020, at a rented home where he was staying while on a four-day trip to Los Angeles

TITLE: White House blames Trump for chaotic Afghanistan withdrawal
SUMMARY: The White House has released a new report into the U.S. withdrawal from Afghanistan, blaming decisions that the Trump administration made for the chaos that unfolded at Kabul International Airport in August 2021. NBC News’ Allie Raffa breaks down the main takeaways from the report and how it could impact a Republican led investigation into the withdrawal.&nbsp

TITLE: Justice Thomas accepted trips from GOP donor, report says
SUMMARY: According to an article released by ProPublica, Supreme Court Justice Clarence Thomas accepted luxury trips from conservative billionaire Harlan Crow without disclosing them. NBC News’ Lawrence Hurley explains what ethical concerns are raised in the report and whether Thomas has responded to the claims.&nbsp

TITLE: U.S. delegates travel to Taiwan despite tensions with China
SUMMARY: Despite rising tensions with China, a bipartisan group of U.S. delegates met with Taiwanese officials in Taipei just days after House Speaker Kevin McCarthy met with Taiwan’s president in California. NBC News’ Janis Mackey Frayer explains what the meetings were focused on and how they could impact relations between the U.S. and China

TITLE: U.S. economy adds 236,000 jobs in March, showing slowdown
SUMMARY: The U.S. economy added 236,000 jobs in the month of March, lower than the previous month, with the unemployment rate dipping slightly to 3.5% according to the Bureau of Labor Statistics jobs report. NBC's Brian Cheung and Caleb Silver break down the report

TITLE: Motley Crue guitarist Mick Mars files lawsuit against band, says he was gaslit and pushed out of group
SUMMARY: Mars’ lawsuit alleges that the group — particularly Nikki Sixx, had a pattern of belittling him for years, telling him he had cognitive issues and insulting him about alleged poor playing on tour, including a stadium outing he completed with the band in 2022

TITLE: WWE apologizes for using Auschwitz footage in pro WrestleMania promo
SUMMARY: The pro wrestling body said it moved quickly after learning about the offensive gaffe, adding: "We apologize for this error

TITLE: Son of controversial Florida data scientist charged with making alleged school threats
SUMMARY: Multiple students in the area of Navarre, Florida, spoke to deputies about seeing posts the son of Rebekah Jones had allegedly shared on Snapchat and Discord
